"p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }\n"
"</style></head><body style=\" font-family:\'Helvetica\'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;\">\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600;\">Instruction for Data</span></p>\n"
"<p style=\"-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><br /></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-family:\'.SF NS Text\'; font-size:13pt;\">In the Data tab of the Pridentifier, you can load the data of classes you want to learn from.</span></p>\n"
"<p style=\"-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:\'.SF NS Text\'; font-size:13pt;\"><br /></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-family:\'.SF NS Text\'; font-size:13pt; font-weight:600;\">How-To Guide:</span></p>\n"
"<p style=\"-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><br /></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-family:\'.SF NS Text\'; font-size:13pt;\">1. Prepare the images. Create a folder in which you create as much folders as classes you want to classify later. The name of the folders will be interpreted as class names later. Then, in every class folder, add the images, you want to use for the analysis step in advance.</span></p>\n"
"<p style=\"-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><br /></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-family:\'.SF NS Text\'; font-size:13pt;\">2. Click \'Load\' in the Data tab. Then, choose the top level folder.</span></p>\n"
"<p style=\"-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><br /></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-family:\'.SF NS Text\'; font-size:13pt;\">3. As result, for every class the amount of found images and the amount of segments in that the images can be fragmented are shown in the widget.</span></p>\n"
"<p style=\"-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:\'.SF NS Text\'; font-size:13pt;\"><br /></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-family:\'.SF NS Text\'; font-size:13pt; font-weight:600;\">Parameter</span><span style=\" font-family:\'.SF NS Text\'; font-size:13pt;\">:</span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-family:\'.SF NS Text\'; font-size:13pt;\">Additionally, you can configure the segment size on that the analysis is computed later on. Depending on this segment size, the load function (after click on Load button) computes the amount of segments it can cut the images into for each class.</span></p>\n"
"<p style=\"-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:\'.SF NS Text\'; font-size:13pt;\"><br /></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-family:\'.SF NS Text\'; font-size:13pt;\">----------------------------------------------------</span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-family:\'.SF NS Text\'; font-size:13pt; font-style:italic;\">Please note when acquiring the data:</span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-family:\'.SF NS Text\'; font-size:13pt;\">- the scanned images must all be scanned with the same scale</span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-family:\'.SF NS Text\'; font-size:13pt;\">- image format should be .png, .jpg or .tiff</span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-family:\'.SF NS Text\'; font-size:13pt;\">- if all classes\' prints are printed on the same paper and scanned with the same scanner would be optimal. Otherwise, try to use different paper for all printers not only for one printer (see also \'About &gt; Application Fields\')</span></p>\n"
"<p style=\"-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:\'.SF NS Text\'; font-size:13pt;\"><br /></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-family:\'.SF NS Text\'; font-size:13pt; font-style:italic;\">Please note when preparing the data folder:</span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-family:\'.SF NS Text\'; font-size:13pt;\">- the structure of folders and images must be as described above</span></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-family:\'.SF NS Text\'; font-size:13pt;\">- only images within that class folders will be used (no image in sub-folders are loaded)</span></p>\n"
"<p style=\"-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:\'.SF NS Text\'; font-size:13pt;\"><br /></p>\n"
"<p style=\" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><span style=\" font-family:\'.SF NS Text\'; font-size:13pt;\">This is the structure as Pridentifer expects:</span></p>\n"
"<p style=\"-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:\'.SF NS Text\'; font-size:13pt;\"><br /></p>\n"
